<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<theorem xmlns="Theorem"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         type="Proposition"
         id="Thm_NoSolution"
         xsi:schemaLocation="Theorem file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle2.5/mod/msm/XSLTdocuments/Theorem.xsd">
   <caption>No solution</caption>
   <associate type="Illustration">
      <showme.pack.ref showmePackID="Illstrtn_LinearEqsNoSolution"/>
      <info>
         <para>
            <para.body>How to recognize a system of linear equations with no solution.</para.body>
         </para>
      </info>
   </associate>
   <statement.theorem>
      <para>
         <para.body>Suppose a system of linear equations is equivalent to an RREF-matrix with a leading 1 in its augmentation column.</para.body>
      </para>
      <math.display>
         <latex>
				
\begin{array}{ccccccccccccccc|c}
0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; * &amp; \cdots &amp; * &amp; 0 &amp; * &amp; \cdots &amp; * &amp; 0 &amp; * &amp; \cdots &amp; * &amp; {\color{blue} 0 } \\
0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; * &amp; \cdots &amp; * &amp; 0 &amp; * &amp; \cdots &amp; * &amp; {\color{blue} 0 } \\
\vdots &amp;   &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp; \vdots &amp; {\color{blue} \vdots } \\
\vdots &amp;   &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp; \vdots &amp; {\color{blue} \vdots } \\
0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; * &amp; \cdots &amp; * &amp; {\color{blue} 0 } \\
0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; {\color{blue} 1 } \\
\vdots &amp;   &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp;   &amp; \vdots &amp; &amp;     &amp; \vdots &amp; {\color{blue} \vdots } \\
0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; \cdots &amp; 0 &amp; {\color{blue} 0 }
\end{array}
					
			</latex>
      </math.display>
      <para>
         <para.body>Then the system has no solution.</para.body>
      </para>
   </statement.theorem>
   <proof type="Proof">
      <proof.block>
         <para>
            <para.body>We know that the RREF-matrix in question corresponds to a system of linear equations whose solutions agree with the original system. Now if the RREF-matrix contains a leading one in its augmentation column, the row containing this leading 1 reads:</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.display>
            <latex>0 \ \cdots\ 0\ |\  1</latex>
         </math.display>
         <para>
            <para.body>The corresponding linear equation reads</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.display>
            <latex>0\cdot x_1 + \cdots + 0\cdot x_n= 1</latex>
         </math.display>
         <para>
            <para.body>Regardless of the number values substituted for the variables <math>
                  <latex>x_1,\dots ,x_n</latex>
               </math>, the left hand side of this equation is always <math>
                  <latex>0\neq 1</latex>
               </math>. Therefore this equation has no solution. So the entire system has no solution either.</para.body>
         </para>
      </proof.block>
   </proof>
</theorem>
